10731150@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The Russian alphabet consists of 33 letters.@1@7@@oe@30-11-2008
10731160@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The following table gives their upper case forms, along with [[help:IPA|IPA]] values for each letter's typical sound:@1@17@@oe@30-11-2008
10731170@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Older letters of the Russian alphabet include <>, which merged to <е> ({{IPA|/e/}}); <і> and <>, which both merged to <и>({{IPA|/i/}}); <>, which merged to <ф> ({{IPA|/f/}}); and <>, which merged to <я> ({{IPA|/ja/}} or {{IPA|/ʲa/}}).@1@36@@oe@30-11-2008
10731180@unknown@formal@none@1@S@While these older letters have been abandoned at one time or another, they may be used in this and related articles.@1@21@@oe@30-11-2008
10731190@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The [[yer]]s <ъ> and <ь> originally indicated the pronunciation of ''ultra-short'' or ''reduced'' {{IPA|/ŭ/}}, {{IPA|/ĭ/}}.@1@15@@oe@30-11-2008
